@node shareware "Shareware notice:"
@pevious disclaimer
@next history

	@{b}SinED is shareware!:@{ub}
	--------------------

	Yes, @{b}SinED II 2.10@{ub} indeed is shareware. I'm strongly encouraging you to
	register this program. By doing so you encourage me to continue the
	development of @{b}SinED II 2.10@{ub}. Support the shareware concept and register
	your quality software today!

	@{b}If you are registering alone:@{ub}
	-----------------------------
	If you are registreing @{b}SinED II 2.10@{ub} for yourself alone you have two
	possibilities. Pay the registration fee in Finnish marks (FIM) which
	costs 80 FIM or send your own currency worth of 100 FIM. The second
	payment method is a little bit higher because I've to change the
	money myself and that costs 20 FIM each time. 100 FIM is approximately
	20 USD (US Dollar) or 35 DEM (Deutsche Mark) or 15 GBP (Pound
	sterling). Fill the @{" registration form " link /registration.txt/main } and send it with your payment
	to @{" me " link author }.

	@{b}If you are registering in group:@{ub}
	--------------------------------
	If you are registering @{b}SinED II 2.10@{ub} in group which has two or more persons
	you may forget the extra 20 FIM I need in order to exchange to money.
	When registering in group, all of the persons have to fill the
	@{b}registration form@{ub} and the filled forms have to be sent to me in
	the same envelope or package to avoid any misunderstandings. The
	keyfiles are then send to each of you separately, each with own disk.
	The prices go:

	Registrations:	Cost each:	Cost total:
	      2		 75.0 FIM	 150 FIM = 30 USD = 50 DEM = 20 GBP
	      3		 66.6 FIM	 200 FIM = 40 USD = 65 DEM = 25 GBP
	      4		 62.5 FIM	 250 FIM = 50 USD = 80 DEM = 30 GBP
	  5 or more	 50.0 FIM	>250 FIM

	1 USD = 5 FIM, 1 DEM = 3 FIM, 1 GPB = 8 FIM.

	Remember that when registering @{b}SinED II 2.10@{ub}, you register it to your own
	personal use! It may not be used by companies or other similar
	large groups.

	@{b}Remember to fill, print and send the @{" Registration form " link /registration.txt/main }.

	@{b}What you get when you register:@{ub}
	-------------------------------
	- A keyfile that enables you to save your work.
	- Latest version of @{b}SinED II@{ub} if you don't already have it. Remember to
	  state the version you are currently using. However, the latest
	  released @{b}SinED II@{ub} can be found almost always from Aminet.
	- A free disk is you are registering via SMail. The keyfile and the
	  latest @{b}SinED II@{ub} is then sent to you.
	- Full right to use the results that you've created with @{b}SinED II@{ub}
	  anywhere you like.


	@{b}Note these facts when you register:@{ub}
	-----------------------------------
	- My EMail: @{b}jvatjus@ee.oulu.fi@{ub}
	- Place the keyfile in PROGDIR: (it's the same directory where the
	  executable is.)

	Send registrations to following address:

	Jarkko Vatjus-Anttila
	Hoikantie 8 B 7
	90500 Oulu
	Finland


	Thank you.

@endnode

@node gadgets "Gadget information"

	@{b}Gadget information@{ub}
	------------------

	@{b}SinED II 2.10@{ub} has thousand gadgets that do several different things. If you
	have difficulties in figuring out which gadget does what and so on,
	just peek the list below:

	@{b}Sample window:@{ub}
		@{b}Cut@{ub}		Cuts the marked part from waveform and copies
				it in the copybuffer. The marked part is
				removed from the waveform.
		@{b}Copy@{ub}		Copy does the same than Cut but is leaves the
				original waveform unaltered.
		@{b}Paste@{ub}		Paste operation pastes the contents of
				copybuffer to the original waveform. You may
				select whether you want to overwrite or insert
				the data.
		@{b}Swap@{ub}		Swap swaps the contents of copybuffer and the
				mainbuffer.
		@{b}Zm in@{ub}		This one zooms in to the area you have
				marked. If the marked area is smaller than 64
				bytes, @{b}SinED II 2.10@{ub} will use 64 byte range instead.
		@{b}Zm out@{ub}		Zoom out enlarges the view a bit if you had
				previously zoomed in.
		@{b}All@{ub}		All gadget displays the total waveform.
		@{b}Left/Right/both@{ub}	This gadget lets you to select which channel
				of the sample is affected when you edit it.
				If the sample is in mono mode, this gadget has
				no effect. Note too that Upsample, Downsample
				and Cleanup are not affected by this switch.
				If the sample is in stereo -mode, both of the
				channels are *always* altered!

	@{b}Playsample window:@{ub}
		@{b}Play waveform@{ub}	This gadget playbacks the whole waveform
				without displaying the progress meter. if the
				sample is in stereo mode, both channels are
				playbacked.
		@{b}Play display@{ub}	This gadget plays the current waveform that is
				displayed. The progress meter is visible too.
		@{b}Play range@{ub}	This playbacks the selected range.
		@{b}Stop playback@{ub}	Just what it says.
		@{b}Play L. wavefrm@{ub}	Plays the left channel waveform in total.
		@{b}Play L. display@{ub}	Plays the left channel display.
		@{b}Play L. range@{ub}	Plays the range you've selected for left
				channel.
		@{b}Play R. wavefrm	\\@{ub} 
		@{b}Play R. display	|-@{ub} These three do the same for Right channel.
		@{b}Play R. range	/@{ub}

	@{b}Drum generator:@{ub}
		@{b}Gadget matrix@{ub}	These gadgets let you to describe the sample
				sequence you want @{b}SinED II 2.10@{ub} to calculate. Each
				horizontal line presents one sample sequence
				and each vertical line one time interval.
		@{b}Delay@{ub}		Lets you to define the speed factor for the
				drummachine mixing process.
		@{b}Calculate@{ub}	This one commands @{b}SinED II 2.10@{ub} to calculate the
				current sample sequence.
		@{b}Clear@{ub}		Cleans up the sequences you have entered.

	@{b}Effect Window:@{ub}
		See descriptions in @{" effects " link effects } page.

	@{b}Wave Window:@{ub}
		See descriptions in @{" waves " link waves } page.

@endnode


